node.text: The @Roger_Dubuis Excalibur Spider Pirelli. A personal favorite color combo 🔥🔥 This is a Roger Dubuis world premiere with the ingenious Quick Release System allowing easy and quick interchangeability of all three components of the watch - from bezel, crown to strap, with a simple click. Available with three additional kits in red, white or blue – the inimitable Pirelli color codes, to get the watch transformed from a full black to a pop of bold color, in a click. Another cool feature is the strap which is made of winning motorsport tyre rubber from real races 🏁 #RogerDubuis #NoRulesOurGame #Pirelli

node.text: @the.realwatchman with a great description: “The Schneider-era #Breitling watches often get a bad rap because people view them as “busy” or “blingy.” That’s definitely not the case with the #BreitlingHeadwind. A classy design that’s still 100% Breitling. I recently learned that the crisp dial markings are made by an etching technique that exposes the underlying silver base dial. Of course, you can’t overlook the white gold Wings logo and the full day module at 12 o’clock”. 🙌🏼 #Breitling #BreitlingWatch

node.text: To celebrate half a decade of #speedytuesday, Omega in collaboration with Fratellowatches created the first speedytuesday limited edition watch. Quickly followed by another limited edition called the Ultraman. For those of you who don’t know about the story behind, let me explain it quickly. Speedytuesday is a movement created on social media, that aims at people to post an Omega Speedmaster timepiece every tuesday. This movement has grown to a big thing on channels such as Instagram and the watch was designed to celebrate its fifth anniversary #Omega #Speedmaster
